Step 1: dotnet new webapi -n EmpManagment
        cd EmpManagment

Step 2: dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.InMemory

Step 3: Create Models/Product.cs for the Product model
        Create Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs for the database context
        Create Controllers/ProductsController.cs for the CRUD operations

Step 4: dotnet add package Swashbuckle.AspNetCore
        dotnet add package Swashbuckle.AspNetCore.SwaggerUI

Step 5: dotnet add package Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL
        dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design

Step 6: (After Doing Code & Set Connection String)
        dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate
        dotnet ef database update

Step 7: After That there is one JSON file in data folder which contains world's all Country , State & Cities Data,
	If You Want to Insert In You PostgreSQL DataBase You Have To Run insert_data.py File With Your Changes , Which Is Located In Script Folder. 